To those who get crashing when calibrating here's the fix. Before clicking on continue to start calibration, make sure u are in a dead quiet environment. Then give it at least 15 seconds for bars to lower. Then turn up your pink noise. It should work fine then.

I use this mostly for ringing out monitors in live shows, but it's handy to use throughout the show to monitor for problems and help guide EQ decisions. Easily worth the price for the pro version.   It could only be improved by having a more customizable (i.e., you can set the frequencies monitored ) 31-band setting; the 31-band EQ is common in live setups. The 30-band setting doesn't quite map to my rack EQ. But this is a minor point; it's close enough!
Simple,  solid and ready for work.  I've been a professional audio engineer for nearly a decade and this little app still impresses me.

This tool looks good, and really speeds up the process of identifying nasty tones and eliminating them without having the magic ears some audio engineers are blessed with.  Had an issue with my new tablet, and the dev responded and fixed it in just 1 day. Massive ups to the dev!  For those that whine that this is inaccurate, this is a tool for live audio engineers to quickly identify what you are hearing. You have to remember that the internal mics are the problem. If you need accuracy, get a $1000 reference mic and plug it into your device and then you can actually argue with the accuracy. This is not a replacement for the real thing, this is a application that allows you to get a few of the most useful base functions of the real thing without the cost and form factor associated.

It may be that I need to better calibrate this app to my HTC One, but my results were only so-so. I used the app to adjust my 13-band kenwood excelon, and ended up wanting my old EQ, set using Octave rta on iOS.  I'm considering AudioTool with Dayton Audio iMM-6 mic,next, as that combo has a prebuilt calibration and the Dayton mic is quite cheap. If that doesn't work, I'll be borrowing a friend's iPhone for an hour!
